	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Johannesburg – A fire ravaged a building on the corner of Albertina Sisulu Road and Troye Street in the Johannesburg CBD on Tuesday, emergency services said. - Are you there, or are you affected? Send us your eyewitness accounts and photos. "A few shops were on fire," said Johannesburg Emergency Management Services spokesperson Nana Radebe. Three fire trucks arrived at the scene and extinguished the blaze. Once the scene was cleared, shopkeepers started salvaging items from the building.        24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  